00:00:00.029 --> 00:00:02.019 align:undefined
<c.cue-0>Principle of consistency. </c>

cue-1
00:00:02.660 --> 00:00:06.659 align:undefined
<c.cue-1>Do you have a friend or colleague who repeatedly asks for small favors </c>

cue-2
00:00:06.670 --> 00:00:10.609 align:undefined
<c.cue-2>such as financial assistance or other forms of help? And because the requests </c>

cue-3
00:00:10.619 --> 00:00:14.329 align:undefined
<c.cue-3>are not too demanding, then you feel obligated to comply with their requests. </c>

cue-4
00:00:14.979 --> 00:00:18.399 align:undefined
<c.cue-4>If such individuals eventually request a more significant </c>

cue-5
00:00:18.409 --> 00:00:21.409 align:undefined
<c.cue-5>favor, you are more likely to grant their request. </c>

cue-6
00:00:22.040 --> 00:00:25.540 align:undefined
<c.cue-6>Fraudsters exploit people's tendency to remain consistent by </c>

cue-7
00:00:25.549 --> 00:00:28.969 align:undefined
<c.cue-7>requesting something minor in an initial email and then gradually </c>

cue-8
00:00:28.979 --> 00:00:31.739 align:undefined
<c.cue-8>escalating their demands in subsequent messages. </c>

cue-9
00:00:32.439 --> 00:00:36.310 align:undefined
<c.cue-9>One example of the principle of consistency in the context of a phishing </c>

cue-10
00:00:36.319 --> 00:00:40.189 align:undefined
<c.cue-10>attack could be when an attacker sends an initial email asking the victim </c>

cue-11
00:00:40.200 --> 00:00:41.340 align:undefined
<c.cue-11>to fill out a survey, </c>

cue-12
00:00:42.130 --> 00:00:46.029 align:undefined
<c.cue-12>the victim completes the survey providing personal information such as </c>

cue-13
00:00:46.040 --> 00:00:47.830 align:undefined
<c.cue-13>their name and email address. </c>

cue-14
00:00:48.540 --> 00:00:52.459 align:undefined
<c.cue-14>Later, the attacker sends a follow up email posing as a trustworthy </c>

cue-15
00:00:52.470 --> 00:00:56.139 align:undefined
<c.cue-15>organization and asks the victim to enter their credit card information to </c>

cue-16
00:00:56.150 --> 00:00:59.889 align:undefined
<c.cue-16>complete a purchase, citing their previous completion of the survey as </c>

cue-17
00:00:59.900 --> 00:01:01.299 align:undefined
<c.cue-17>evidence of their interest. </c>

cue-18
00:01:02.090 --> 00:01:05.980 align:undefined
<c.cue-18>The victim may be more likely to comply with this request due to the principle of </c>

cue-19
00:01:05.989 --> 00:01:09.849 align:undefined
<c.cue-19>consistency as they have already taken a small step towards providing </c>

cue-20
00:01:09.860 --> 00:01:11.800 align:undefined
<c.cue-20>personal information.</c>